Creating an existential-themed web game in a single HTML file involves crafting a simple narrative and interactive elements that provoke thought about existence, meaning, and choices. Below is a basic web app structure that presents an interactive game with existential themes, embedded CSS for styling, and JavaScript for functionality.

You can copy and paste the code below into a `.html` file and open it in your browser.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>The Existential Game</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            background-color: #121212;
            color: #fff;
            text-align: center;
            padding: 50px;
        }
        button {
            background-color: #3E50B4;
            color: white;
            border: none;
            padding: 15px 25px;
            cursor: pointer;
            margin: 10px;
            border-radius: 5px;
            font-size: 16px;
        }
        button:hover {
            background-color: #1A237E;
        }
        #story {
            margin: 20px 0;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>The Existential Game</h1>
    <div id="story">You are at a crossroads in life. One path leads to certainty and comfort, the other to chaos and uncertainty. Which do you choose?</div>
    <button onclick="choosePath('certainty')">Take the Path of Certainty</button>
    <button onclick="choosePath('chaos')">Venture into Chaos</button>
    <div id="output"></div>

    <script>
        function choosePath(path) {
            const output = document.getElementById('output');
            let response;

            if (path === 'certainty') {
                response = "You followed the path of certainty, but soon realized it was paved with unchallenged routines and stagnation. Did you trade your curiosity for comfort?";
            } else {
                response = "You embraced the chaos, where every moment is unpredictable. Yet, amidst the uncertainty, you find creativity and passion. Is there a beauty in the chaos?";
            }

            output.innerHTML = `<p>${response}</p>`;
            output.innerHTML += '<button onclick="continueJourney()">Continue Your Journey</button>';
        }

        function continueJourney() {
            const output = document.getElementById('output');
            output.innerHTML += `<p>Life is a series of choices. Do you wish to reflect on your journey or continue without looking back?</p>`;
            output.innerHTML += `
                <button onclick="reflect()">Reflect on Journey</button>
                <button onclick="moveForward()">Move Forward</button>`;
        }

        function reflect() {
            const output = document.getElementById('output');
            output.innerHTML = `<p>You take a moment to ponder the choices you've made. Was there ever a right path? Perhaps the exploration itself holds the meaning.</p>`;
            output.innerHTML += '<button onclick="restart()">Restart the Game</button>';
        }

        function moveForward() {
            const output = document.getElementById('output');
            output.innerHTML = `<p>As you move forward, life continues. Each step you take is a question unanswered, leading to new choices and existential quandaries.</p>`;
            output.innerHTML += '<button onclick="restart()">Restart the Game</button>';
        }

        function restart() {
            const output = document.getElementById('output');
            document.getElementById('story').innerHTML = "You are at a crossroads in life. One path leads to certainty and comfort, the other to chaos and uncertainty. Which do you choose?";
            output.innerHTML = '';
        }
    </script>
</body>
</html>
```

This game poses choices that reflect common existential themesâ€”comfort versus chaos, reflection versus action. It encourages users to think deeply about their life choices and implications. Feel free to expand upon the story, choices, and outcomes to create a richer experience!
